20/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The IMF has asked the government in Ankara to raise taxes to cover recent spending increases, Dow Jones Newswires reported Monday (19 January), citing insider information. 
An IMF team is visiting Turkey to examine implementation of its austerity stabilisation programme. 
The government recently increased minimum wages and pensions by more than the 12 per cent ceiling, agreed upon with the IMF. 
Turkey has also announced plans to cut the VAT on certain items. 
(Dow Jones - 19/01/04)
